56. What are all the Functions available to sort a PHP array?
ANSWER
1. Sorting Indexed Arrays (by values):

sort(array $array)

Sorts array in ascending order.

Does not preserve keys (reindexes the array).

rsort(array $array)

Sorts array in descending order.

Does not preserve keys.

✅ 2. Sorting Associative Arrays by Values:

asort(array $array)

Sorts array by values in ascending order.

Preserves key-value association.

arsort(array $array)

Sorts array by values in descending order.

Preserves keys.

✅ 3. Sorting Associative Arrays by Keys:

ksort(array $array)

Sorts array by keys in ascending order.

Preserves key-value association.

krsort(array $array)

Sorts array by keys in descending order.

Preserves keys.

✅ 4. Custom/User-Defined Sorting:

usort(array &$array, callable $callback)

Sorts indexed array using a custom comparison function.

Does not preserve keys.

uasort(array &$array, callable $callback)

Sorts associative array by values using a user-defined function.

Preserves keys.

uksort(array &$array, callable $callback)

Sorts associative array by keys using a user-defined function.

Preserves keys.

✅ 5. Natural Order Sorting:

natsort(array &$array)

Sorts array using natural "human" order (e.g., file1, file2, file10).

Preserves keys.

natcasesort(array &$array)

Same as natsort() but case-insensitive.

Preserves keys.
